							<p>TS Can Van Luc and the author of the BIDV Training and Research Institute said that the concept of electronic money / e-money today in the world is often understood in a fairly wide range. The definitions are a bit complicated, which can cause confusion about the content of cryptocurrencies, are difficult to distinguish from cryptocurrencies, digital currencies and even mobile money.</p>
							<p>In fact, cryptocurrencies have been identified and clearly distinguished from other currencies through four main characteristics. First of all, cryptocurrencies must be legal tender. Accordingly, cryptocurrencies have all three functions of money: store value, exchange of medium and exchange (unit of account). At the same time, cryptocurrencies are always expressed as the value of a country's fiat currency (for example, VND, USD, SGD ...). Besides, cryptocurrencies are also guaranteed by the Central Bank.</p>
							<p>Secondly, cryptocurrencies can be issued by banks or also by non-bank organizations. Therefore, to ensure the safety for users, countries always have very strict regulations for cryptocurrency issuers. For banks, the central bank has a strict system of operational safety, risk management, required reserve ratios, deposit insurance, etc. For non-bank organizations, the central bank has regulations on licensing, supervision ... and usually requires deposit at the banking system (corresponding to the amount issued with a certain percentage). .</p>
							<p>Thirdly, cryptocurrencies have a monetary regimes mechanism of the central bank. Accordingly, cryptocurrencies issued by banks will be guaranteed by the required reserve ratio at the central bank, while cryptocurrencies issued by non-bank organizations will be guaranteed by deposit mechanism at the system. banking system (with a certain margin ratio). Typically, the margin ratio will be much higher than the required reserve ratio as the safety rules applicable to these institutions are much lower than banks. The margin ratio in some countries with prudent approach is at 100%. This is also the key difference between bank deposits (bank deposits) and electronic money (e-money).</p>
							<p>Fourth, cryptocurrencies are only stored in electronic products of two types: (i) hardware (hard-ware based products) such as chip cards, chip-embedded smartphones and (ii) data-based software (soft-ware based) like Paypal electronic wallet.</p>
							<blockquote>
								"The concept of electronic money / e-money today in the world is often understood in a fairly wide range."
								<span>Oliver Dale </span>
